cs.CE, cs.MS, cs.NA, cs.SE, cs.ME 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper proposes a thermal finite element model for the simulation of metal powder bed fusion additive manufacturing processes, which involves numerical methods and simulations in engineering and science. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper discusses numerical methods for the treatment of phase change and latent heat effects, which are relevant to mathematical software development. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper compares and evaluates different numerical methods for phase change and latent heat, which falls under the scope of numerical analysis. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a novel variant of the heat integration scheme, which can be considered as a software engineering contribution. 
- cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering): The paper focuses on the simulation of metal additive manufacturing processes, which is a topic of interest in mechanical engineering.
